video.title: Terrace House: Opening New Doors
video.synopsis: A group of young people -- including a chef, a snowboarder and an ice hockey player -- gather in the Karuizawa woods while pursuing their dreams.

episodes.synopsis: Six strangers gather in a house in Karuizawa. Aged 19 to 31, they've got one thing in common: they'll be living together in a beautiful town.
episodes.title: Opening New Doors

episodes.synopsis: As everyone settles in, Yuudai shows off his cooking skills. When some members go out to lunch, he seems to hit it off with one girl in particular.
episodes.title: A New Experience For Her

episodes.synopsis: In the midst of discussing their dreams for the future, Shion gives Ami some advice. Then a group visits Tsubasa's father's restaurant.
episodes.title: Captain Tsubasa

episodes.synopsis: Yuudai wants to be independent, but he's struggling. Later, Ami starts crying when Yuudai asks her bluntly what she wants to do with her life.
episodes.title: The Reason She Cried

episodes.synopsis: Mizuki grows increasingly skeptical of Yuudai, who keeps buying things using his father's credit card. Tsubasa and Shion head to Kusatsu Onsen.
episodes.title: Cocky Kid

episodes.synopsis: Yuudai vows to make changes and finds a restaurant to work at, while Ami makes some career decisions. The two of them go on a date in Karuizawa.
episodes.title: First Snowfall

episodes.synopsis: Ami and Yuudai both dissect their date with the other members. Yuudai is taken aback by Ami's attitude towards him the next day.
episodes.title: I Erased Him From My World

episodes.synopsis: Mizuki spends the night in Tokyo with her old boyfriend. Shut out by Ami, Yuudai reconnects with an old girlfriend too, while Takayuki tries to help.
episodes.title: A Man with Different Values

episodes.synopsis: Tsubasa and Shion visit a temple for good luck before her team's big game. Meanwhile, Mizuki makes a decision, and Yuudai cooks for a house party.
episodes.title: She's the MVP

episodes.synopsis: Takayuki takes Ami to a breathtaking cafe, while Tsubasa's confidence takes a hit after hearing about Shion's ex. On Christmas, new members arrive.
episodes.title: The Christmas Assassinï»¿

episodes.synopsis: Seina and Takayuki take a stroll in Kyu-Karuizawa. When Ami hears about it, she invites Takayuki snowboarding. Then Shion and Tsubasa go ice-skating.
episodes.title: Best Actor in a Supporting Role

episodes.synopsis: When Ami and Takayuki go snowboarding, she tells him something very intriguing. Shion answers a question about Tsubasa, and then it's New Year's.
episodes.title: If Only You Were Five Years Younger

episodes.synopsis: Some of the members go snowboarding, but Ami and Takayuki only have eyes for each other. Tsubasa goes to Tokyo to buy Shion a birthday present.
episodes.title: She Asks Too Much For Love

episodes.synopsis: The members throw a birthday party for Ami and Shion, and Takayuki surprises everyone by shaving his mustache. Tsubasa gives Shion his gift privately.
episodes.title: The Birthday That Decided Their Fate

episodes.synopsis: Shohei and Ami go out together, but there isn't really a spark. In the face of Ami's cold attitude, Takayuki starts to regrow his mustache.
episodes.title: The Mustache Tells the Story of Love

episodes.synopsis: Takayuki tells Seina and Shohei that he no longer has feelings for Ami, but Shohei's feelings for her have grown. Ami, meanwhile, makes a choice.
episodes.title: Life is Just a Little Too Late

episodes.synopsis: Just before Ami's scheduled departure, Shohei meets her at the station for a surprise trip to the slopes -- and he's got a plan. A new member arrives.
episodes.title: Sinful Cleavage

episodes.synopsis: It's Valentine's Day, and Tsubasa is about to head to Nagoya for the national championships. Shion has something to tell her before she goes.
episodes.title: Flower Bouquet for My Valentine

episodes.synopsis: With the tournament over, Tsubasa has time to think about her next steps -- including her reply to Shion. Shohei heads into the recording studio.
episodes.title: The Second Attempt

episodes.synopsis: Tsubasa gives Shion her answer. On a snowy day, Mayu and Takayuki talk about love, while Shohei and Seina continue spending time together.
episodes.title: A Fairy on a Split Road

episodes.synopsis: Seina returns from a trip to Korea looking somewhat different. Takayuki and Mayu go out to eat, and Tsubasa makes another decision.
episodes.title: Tune-Up

episodes.synopsis: Two new members arrive: aspiring pilot Noah and Karuizawa native, Yui. Almost immediately, Noah and Mayu head out on a date.
episodes.title: Virgin

episodes.synopsis: Takayuki takes Noah to the yakitori place. Mayu really likes Noah, and she gets nervous when he and Yui plan to spend time together.
episodes.title: Meccha Me Too

episodes.synopsis: Shohei takes Seina out on a birthday dinner. Awkwardness reigns when Mayu's time with Noah goes nowhere. Noah and Yui go on their planned outing.
episodes.title: Kiss Out Of Nowhere

episodes.synopsis: Yui keeps trying to patch things up with Mayu. Shohei prepares for an album release show in Shibuya, then asks Yui for some local tips.
episodes.title: The Fallen Angel

episodes.synopsis: Mayu and Noah go on a hike, and when they get back, Mayu has an honest talk with Yui and makes a decision. A new member joins Terrace House.
episodes.title: Better Than You

episodes.synopsis: New member Aya settles into the house, and the members make plans to go camping together. Seina responds surprisingly to Shohei's bold moves.
episodes.title: On the Night of Camp...

episodes.synopsis: Aya and Takayuki head out on a date together. Meanwhile, after a surprising conversation with Shohei, Noah hangs out with Yui once again.
episodes.title: Declaration of War

episodes.synopsis: Yui talks to Shohei about Noah, and then tells Noah off the next day. Shohei makes plans to ask Seina to date him, and Aya asks Shohei for a favor.
episodes.title: Confessing Love at the Chapel

episodes.synopsis: After hearing from Shohei, Noah asks Seina out on a date. During Takayuki's birthday party, Aya talks with him one on one.
episodes.title: A Farce

episodes.synopsis: Aya and Yui grow suspicious about Seina and Noah, and Yui tries to interrogate Seina about it. Shohei prepares an event for the other members.
episodes.title: Rambling Rose

episodes.synopsis: Takayuki gives Aya a gift before he takes her skateboarding. Noah and Seina go on an extremely consequential date, and then a new member arrives.
episodes.title: The Last Love

episodes.synopsis: As Noah and Seina spend a day together, Shunsuke talks about bisexuality with the other members. Takayuki tells Aya a secret.
episodes.title: Itâs Someone Else

episodes.synopsis: On the morning of Seina and Noah's departure, Takayuki shares a decision with the other members, then travels to Tokyo. Some familiar faces return.
episodes.title: Bye Bye, Miss Terrace House

episodes.synopsis: Three new members join the House: skateboarder Kaito, student Maya, and company employee Sota. The next day, Yui and Kaito go grocery shopping.
episodes.title: Young Faces

episodes.synopsis: Maya and Kaito go out to a soba shop to try the Karuizawa specialty. Yui and Kaito make plans to go to a skate park so she can learn to skateboard.
episodes.title: Take Shelter from the Rain

episodes.synopsis: Aya has a heart-to-heart about her future with Yui. After Sota and Shunsuke spend a day hanging out together, Shunsuke comes to a decision.
episodes.title: First and Last Date

episodes.synopsis: After a farewell breakfast, the members welcome two newcomers: model Risako and ex-soccer player Aio. Then they plan a birthday party for Kaito.
episodes.title: The Goal-Getter and the Goalless

episodes.synopsis: Yui gets job-hunting tips from Sota before he and Risako go out to lunch. At the beach to see Kaito skateboard, the members meet a Hawaii alumnus.
episodes.title: Like a Long Spell of Autumn Rain

episodes.synopsis: Kaito and Yui head to Matsumoto to see Shohei in concert. Aio asks Risako out on another date, as does Sota, while Kaito and Maya go to an art exhibit.
episodes.title: A Man Who Can't be Described in Japanese

episodes.synopsis: Risako visits a lava field with Aio but cancels on a date with Sota. After a beer factory tour, Sota asks Maya on another date, but she refuses.
episodes.title: Embarrassing Rejections

episodes.synopsis: Sota comes to a decision and informs the other housemates. Aio reneges on his invitation to Risako so he can ask Yui on a date to a soccer match.
episodes.title: To Have Become Critical

episodes.synopsis: Masao learns that he snores and Aio and Yui go fishing. The night before Maya's college fashion show, Yui and Risako talk to her about her behavior.
episodes.title: Booger Boy and Snoring Boy

episodes.synopsis: With his feelings growing for Risako, Masao decides to make lunch for her. Kaito and Maya go ice skating, then spend more time together that night.
episodes.title: Only the Apple Was Watching

episodes.synopsis: While out to a bar together, Aio tells Yui his feelings. While Risako is away for work, Maya and Yui discuss their thoughts on her behavior.
episodes.title: Tattling

episodes.synopsis: Masao tries to comfort Risako, whoâs still at odds with the girls. Later, Aio tells Risako the truth about his relationship with Yui.
episodes.title: No Longer a Virgin

episodes.synopsis: Risako makes it clear that she knows how far Yui went with Aio. After going on a glassblowing date, Masao tells Risako his feelings.
episodes.title: Still a Virgin

episodes.synopsis: Masao asks Risako to give him her response at his band's Christmas concert in Fukuoka, but first she talks to his notorious bandmate, Enon Kawatani.
episodes.title: Walking Ritz-Carlton

episodes.synopsis: As previous members celebrate the holidays, Yui's birthday approaches in Karuizawa. Meanwhile, Risako travels to Fukuoka for Masao's show.
episodes.title: Departure Whistle
